wn wrist, and then it became a battle of raw strength.  Glenn realised this would be a battle he would lose,  so he let go of the mans hand while simultaneosly dodging with his head to the right.  The dagger once again hit cloak,  but this time, before the man could pull back again,  Glenn quickly struck the man's ulnar nerve at the back of his elbow with a dextrous chop with his fingers,  this momentarily caused the man to realise his grip on the dagger,  and Glenn used the opurtunity to wrestle the dagger for his own.  The man realising that he was now losing this scuffle,  launched himself backwards of Glenn,  but through the roll on the floor, he had lost his sense of direction,  and with the desperate luanch backwards, hit his head on the wall.  He then crumpled to the floor out cold.  Glenn, took a moment to catch his breath,  but, as reality came back to him, he remembered Sparrow and the others, and once again took off in their direction.   The sight Glenn saw when he reached the encampent filled him with anger and a sense of revenge.  The theifs were taking full advantage of Glenn's wounded comrades.  With a second glance,  however, Glenn noticed among the sprawled human forms on the floor,  than many of them were not his comrades.  Glenn noted how the slime in the wounded affected their fighting.  In Athena,  who was exposed the least, surprisingly ignoring her pain, faught with an extreme  bloodlust that seemded alien to her.  Tehn also,  the more he faught,  the more he seemed to ignore the pain.  And, then there was Murm, he was exposed to slime the most,  plus,  he had previously faught the bugs with demonic stregth and speed,  and now ,he thrashed around in some momentous inner battle.  Finally, it hit Glenn,  the slime  was none other than the rare subtance that one of his old mentors mentioned in one of his lectures.  By now Glenn had forgoten the name,  but he knew its properties.  It caused the the infected to fight in a blood lust till he wore his own body to death through shere exaustion.  Murm had previously faught with all he had,  and was now fighting the last stages in his dreams,  Athena,  who hadnt faught as much before,  was in a rage,  hacking a dead theifs body into pieces,  and Tehn, his own wound was more physical,  which in its own exausted him, affecting his ability to fight, was soon on the path to join Murm in the final stages of unconsienceness.  Glenn now knew what he had to do.  Glenn pulled out a vile from the recesses of his cloak,  it contained a subtance that would cut of the slime's access to the brain,  allowing the infected to take control of their body again.  Glenn silently stalked his way to Murm's side,  and gave him a quick dose by spreading it on some exposed flesh.  He then pondered how he was going to give the dose to Athena in her blood rage, when he saw her give him an opening with her love for her fellow mankind and her moment of sympathy for Sparrow.  After he gave her the dose,  startling her he could tell,  Glenn melted back into the shadows when he realized their was another stranger in the party fighting for them,  Glenn wanted to see if this man would aide Tehn.  However,  Glenn realized that his own curiousty was enough inaction that the last thief had Tehn and Sparrow at sword point.  Glenn was momentarily stunned with knowing this was his friends's end when the huge form of Murm flew ,  stunning the theif in shock and surprise moments before he was tackled and pummeled to the floor.  Glenn, though relieved to see Murm consious and in full command of his senses,  was in complete shock,  &quot;How could he have made such a complete recovery so fast!!!!!  In the state he was in it should of taken at least 3 hours or so...wow...there is something strange about Murm...&quot;  Glenn set those thoughts aside for later and rushed to the more immeadiate needs.  He kneeled and gave a dose to the downed Tehn. As he took care of Tehn he asked the stranger &quot;Your help is greatly appreciated kind sir,  however,  my friends here are greatly injured and I'm afraid I need more help,  mind lending me your aide?  My name is Glenn Tyreson...and yours is...?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sagecoqui>SageCoqui</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.dragid.com/newbuddy.php?id=1874" BORDER=0> at: 10/7/03 8:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfaeryfirealongthenightshore.showUserPublicProfile?gid=orlindurgenhart>OrlinDurgenhart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(10/7/03 10:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffaeryfirealongthenightshorefrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> the new Face</span><hr size=1> &quot;I am Orlin,  the Pleasure is all mine.&quot; Orlin replies with a short bow.  &quot;I am a traveling Bard and heard the fighting to and came to see if I could help.&quot;  Orlin then turns to the rest of the party and begins binding their wounds.  After completing this Orlin walks over to Glen and says &quot;tell my your story...&quot;<br>
