e, Tehn gave half a smile and said, &quot;let us discuss it in the morning, my friends.  I think all of us could use the rest.  There are many forces working in the world right now, but they shall have to wait a few hours, now won't they?&quot;  As he settled back into a sitting position, he grimaced in pain, but thankful that the rage was leaving his blood.  &quot;We will... we need our rest right now...&quot;' <br>
As the remainder of the night slowly passed, Tehn kept fitfully waking up, casting distrustful glances through the camp.  His hunt had been calm for at least three months, and now three major events in the course of one night.  Could one of these men somehow be a spy?  Both Sparrow and Glenn had 'luckily' avoided the slime.  Had they aided him just to enter his circle?  Had the giant realized who he was, and seeing his first approach fail miserably, attempted a different approach?  Perhaps his fears were unfounded, he had been far too careless with his tongue, and many others besides these had heard things that should not have been heard.  Tehn was careful to make sure Glenn, the one still on watch, noticed not his gazes.  Others seemed to be sleeping fitfully as well, perhaps just a side effect of Glenn's medecine.  But then again, Glenn arrived just after the battle had already been decided.  And this newcomer, what of him?  Who prowls the streets besides the bloodied thieves that had been hidden?  Had he somehow been stalking them all along, waiting for his chance to become the hero these wanderers needed, or just seeing an opportunity to follow them in a much easier way.  While the strength of numbers could help greatly, and surely they could all benefit from reaching the library, but what then?  How could he have been so stupid, thinking they could be trusted?  They knew nothing of his suffering, nothing of loss, nothing of betrayal, except of betraying.  He thought briefly of trying to steal away, but Glenn was far too vigilent to miss that, and far too strong resolve to fall asleep...  <br>
The night slowly lessened, without further event, and as dawn finally broke, Tehn woke up and began to make preparations for the day.  Glenn gave him a smile, and promptly fell asleep for a quick nap as the others continued sleeping.  Tehn thought, &quot;I could leave now... but... it doesn't seem as necessary now... perhaps the poison and dark were still clouding my mind... no one can see all ends, we may need each other yet.&quot;  His back was feeling incredibly better, another proof that it may be worth giving them his trust.  <br>
Slowly the others woke up, and as Murm finally broke out of his deep slumber, they made ready to leave.  As they left the town, Tehn said, &quot;We head this way,&quot; setting a tough pace for the amount of sleep they had and all the excitement through the night. <p>______________________________<br>
