Inside lives a man with long white hair and a charming smile. He has wrinkles which speak of many many years gone by, but clear blue eyes that are as quick as a curious child. Wearing many rings, he pets his white and brown tabby cat pondering and reading. When he rises from his chair a large staff comes to his aide and he walks with only a slight hobble. He laughs to himself with a quiet &quot;hohohoo&quot; and wonders if his inn will have any visitors soon, since the air smells like change, and change usually means youthful trouble...<br>
<br>
