eavy iron.  It was opened and she could see nothing but darkness...  The next thing she knew she was bound to a wall by chains and surronded by bugs or humans, whatever they were.  The exchanged a signal throughout the crowd and suddenly the bugs began turning into the awful blue ooze.  The room was at a slant and the goo traveled down to where Athena was bound.  So clawed and scratched and tried to flip or anything to avoid the goo, but it was too late the goo grew on her, burning skin and she bean to take the form of one of the human bugs slowly.  Emersed feet in the ooze became long stick bug legs and so on and so forth until it reached her waist.  Higher and higher it traveled until she screamed.  She opened her eyes and she was in the arms of the giant, Murm.  Sweating and shaking she was at the door of a hostel in the arms of the kind giant.  With a sigh of relieve she spoke, &quot; Thank you Murm&quot; as the giant gave a slight bow of his head.  They was all her newly made friends, Glenn, Tehn, Sparrow, Murm, and an odd new commer she had never seen before.  She called out Glenn's name, recalling that she thought the robbers of the night had given her some kind of drug and she rolled up her sleeve and saw a large rash of some kind, very purple and odd.  She gashped at the sight of her own arm, and fell faint.  <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
If you could slit my throat,<br>
And with my one last gasphing breath,<br>
I'd apologize for bleeding on your shirt.<br>
<br>
