ate a brief breakfast, paid their stay, and quickly made preparations.  They set out of the city, Tehn leading.  They quickly made their way to the outskirts without incident, and were soon in open territory.  The gently rolling hills gave a sense of calm, while occasional trees and small groves of trees still presented an aura of protection and peace.  As they made good time towards their destination, Tehn pulled out a small intricate cylinder, and quickly fingering several places, deftly twisting the various segments and gildings.  He then pulled out what seemed to be a small map and quickly looked at the sun and surrounding environ.  With a contented expression of determination, replaced the map, followed with just as many swift movements to relock the cylinder, and replaced it within his garments.  As they continued onwards, the landscape seemed to grow more desolate, and as the tree cover gradually gave way to barrenness, turned to Sparrow and muttered, &quot;I think we've picked up a tail, something is following us, 5 o clock.  They're still a good distance off though...&quot;<br>
